d and Bret Schulte, The Arkansas Angle, a student-run multimedia magazine.</p>\n<p>The Arkansas Angle is a new publication by the Art and Journalism students of Tom Hapgood and Bret Schulte that uses WordPress as a publishing platform. We’ll discuss how we chose WordPress, how we’re using plugins, why we’re no longer using Flash, the relevance of WordPress to journalism students and other details about this online magazine by University of Arkansas students.</p>\n<div id="v-JhhxJWtj-1" class="video-player">\n</div>\n<br />  <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gocomments/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/comments/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godelicious/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/delicious/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gofacebook/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/facebook/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gotwitter/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/twitter/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/gostumble/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/stumble/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/godigg/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/digg/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <a rel="nofollow" href="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/goreddit/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/"><img alt="" border="0" src="http://feeds.wordpress.com/1.0/reddit/wptv.wordpress.com/6738/" /></a> <img alt="" border="0" src="http://stats.wordpress.com/b.gif?host=wordpress.tv&blog=5089392&post=6738&subd=wptv&ref=&feed=1" width="1