(706, 0, '_transient_dash_aa95765b5cc111c56d5993d476b1c2f0', '<div class="rss-widget"><ul><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2011/08/survey-data-released/'' title=''Over on WordPress.org we’ve released the raw data behind the survey. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Survey data released</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://wordpress.org/news/2011/08/state-of-the-word/'' title=''This has been an exciting year for WordPress. We’ve grown to power 14.7% of the top million websites in the world, up from 8.5%, and the latest data show 22 out of every 100 new active domains in the US are running WordPress. We also conducted our first ever user and developer survey, which got over 18,000 responses from all over the world: We found a few in [&hellip;]''>Dev Blog: State of the Word</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/weblogtoolscollection/UXMP/~3/Zg9DDW80KFs/'' title=''New plugins Color Manager adds an option panel to the front-page which enables your client or theme users to pick the colors and see the results live in the page. Social Media Tabs allows you to add facebook, google +1, buzz, twitter and RSS profiles and feeds to any widget area with stylish sliding tabs. WordPress Snap is a simple shortcode for displaying a [&hellip;]''>Weblog Tools Collection: WordPress Plugin Releases for 8/19</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://lorelle.wordpress.com/2011/08/18/managing-multiple-authors-managing-writers-in-a-multiple-author-blog/'' title=''In this series on managing multiple bloggers in WordPress, I want to now focus on the content, specifically managing the editorial voice and purpose of a site with multiple bloggers. There is a huge caveat to this topic. Every blog is unique, as are all the voices within it. It is often that uniqueness that [&hellip;]''>Lorelle on WP: Managing Multiple Authors: Managing Writers in a Multiple Author Blog</a></li><li><a class=''rsswidget'' href=''http://ma.tt/2011/08/presidential-candidates-on-wp/'' title=''6 of the 10 Republican presidential candidates are using WordPress, the other 4 are on Drupal, which means all 10 are on an Open Source CMS. [&hellip;]''>Matt: Presidential Candidates on WP</a></li></ul></div>', 'no'),
