(19, 1, '2011-05-08 20:53:18', '2011-05-08 19:53:18', 'I have made a simple progressbar class.\r\n\r\n<a title="Example page" href="http://test.rpg-stars.de/developing/js/progressbar/example.html">Example</a>\r\n\r\nHow-to:\r\n<pre escaped="true" class="brush: js">var myProgress = new Progress({\r\n ''element'' : ''id'',// required\r\n ''size'' : [height,width],// required\r\n ''className'' : ''classOftheProgressBar'', // not required\r\n ''initialValue'' : 0, //default,not required\r\n ''barBackground'' : true // default, not required //describes if it has a background or not\r\n });</pre>\r\nIt doesnt require jquery, you can just put it right into the page.', 'Progressbar', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'progressbar', '', '', '2011-05-08 21:08:47', '2011-05-08 20:08:47', '', 0, 'http://dev.rpg-stars.de/?p=19', 0, 'post', '', 0),
